        <hl1>THE MARKETS: COMMODITIES</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Coffee surges as frost in Brazil heightens speculation that crops of world's largest grower will be damaged; in New York, coffee for September delivery rises 9.7 cents, or 10.5 percent, to $1.022 a pound; graph; chart (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>COFFEE SOARS. Coffee surged as frost in Brazil heightened speculation that crops of the world's largest grower would be damaged. In New York, coffee for September delivery rose 9.7 cents, or 10.5 percent, to $1.022 a pound.</p>
      </block>
